HEADWORD: Exscind
<hw>Ex*scind"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Exscinded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Exscinding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>exscindere</ets>;
<ets>ex</ets> out, from + <ets>scindere</ets> to cut.]</ety> <def>To cut
off; to separate or expel from union; to extirpate.</def>
<rj><au>Barrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The second presbytery of Philadelphia was also
<qex>exscinded</qex> by that Assembly.</q> <rj><qau>Am.
Cyc.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

